com.darkfoxdev.tesi.targetlint.checks.operations

Class ReferenceMatchCheckOperation<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.darkfoxdev.tesi.targetlint.checks.operations.CheckOperation
      • com.darkfoxdev.tesi.targetlint.checks.operations.ReferenceMatchCheckOperation<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type parameter

    public class ReferenceMatchCheckOperation<T>
extends CheckOperation
    This check operation is defined by a second target and an operation of type Function<Match,T>. The check(...) method applies the operation to both the input matches and second target's matches. Output matches are the ones for which exists a match (at least one) in the second target that, once applied the operation, give the same result.
    For example, in a BroadcastReceiver, we can look for registrations without unregistrations:
    • first target targets the registerReceiver(...) method
    • second target targets the unregisterReceiver(...) method
    • create a new ReferenceMatchCheckOperation with an operation that extract the argument name from the call
    • negate the check operation so that return matches for which doesn't exists an unregisterReceiver(...) call
